modules.description: Provides operations for defining and executing continuous workflows, including fetching repository commits, building code, running tests, and deploying binaries. Works with Git repositories, commit hashes, and build artifacts. Used to automate CI/CD pipelines and ensure build statuses reflect the latest changes in real time.

Creates a channel from a Slack webhook URI and posts messages to it, updating a key only when the message changes. Operates on URI values and string-based messages wrapped in a Current.t type. Used to notify Slack channels of build statuses or system events with minimal redundant updates.
